title: Election Night Forecasting Models
text: different analyses, election data often needs different format. smallest unit election data, corresponds dataframe row “longest” format, consists : state, uppercase USPS abbreviation state. STATE_AP constant package can used map abbreviations Associated Press state abbreviations display purposes. election, date particular election, stored CSV YYYY-MM-DD. jurisdiction, character identifier jurisdiction office. Use "US" President, otherwise state abbreviation, city county name. contest, lowercase character identifier type contest. Use "pres", "sen", "house", "gov", "stsen", "sthouse", etc (full listing CONTESTS variable). Suffix contest _dem _rep Democratic Republican primaries. district, positive integer identifier district number office. Use NA necessary, 1 -large districts. candidate, character identifier candidate. Recommended format: "<last>, <first> [<middle>][, <suffix]" proper capitalization. Can NA necessary. party, lowercase character identifier party candidate. One "dem" "rep" "ind" "oth". PARTIES constant package can used map abbreviations full party names. time, timestamp data record. stage, type data. Recommended format: "final", "partial", "reported", "expected", "test". Integer editorial stage also acceptable. method, vote method reported. One "eday", “early”, "mail", “abs”, “adv” (combo early, mail, absentee), "prov", "". VOTE_METHODS constant package can used map abbreviations full names. geo, unique geographic character identifier. Recommended: FIPS code counties, GEOID similar precincts, "" race-wide data. votes, non-negative numeric value vote count. Character vectors can also factors. value "" rserved indicate aggregation column. Additional columns permitted. recommended names possible additional columns include: - past_*, past vote data - flag, character idnetifier quality control flags

Republican minus Democratic default. time model, character identifier prediction model. model_conf, character identifier interval prediction method. confidence credible interval level clear field.
